The isolated compounds were tested for their antioxidant activity against ABTS radical, DPPH radical scavenging and FRAP (
Table 5
). Antioxidant activity ranging from 543.71 to 1311.09 mmol Trolox equivalent/g sample for ABST radical, 370.67–545.03 mmol Trolox equivalent/g sample for DPPH and 103.14–1098.77 mmol Trolox equivalent/g sample for FRAP were observed for the isolated compounds (compounds 3–8).

The comprehensive details on the extraction protocol were reported in previous report (
Auberon et al., 2018
, 
2019
, 
2020
). Centrifugal partition chromatography (CPC) of the EtOAc soluble fraction (
10.93 g
) afforded 14 fractions. The fractions 9–13 (
3.57 g
) were further separated using Sephadex LH-20 column eluted with MeOH. Sub-fractions 9b (
72.4 mg
) and 9d (
63.5 mg
) were purified on a semi-preparative RP-HPLC using a gradient elution (H 
2
O (A) and MeCN (B) both containing 0.05% formic acid; 45% B for 5 min, 45–50% B for 35 min, 50–100% B for 5 min, 100% B for 5 min at a flow rate of 14 mL/min) to yield 7 (
5.8 mg
) and 10 (
3.8 mg
).

Similarly sub-fraction 10b (
206 mg
) was further purified using semi-preparative RP HPLC (using a gradient elution of 45% B for 5 min, 45–55% B for 40 min, 55–100% B for 5 min and 100% B for 5 min at a flow rate 14 mL/min) to give 1 (2.0 mg) and 3 (
4.7 mg
). 2 (
2.1 mg
), 4 (
9.2 mg
) and 5 (
